{
	"info": {
		"name": "X-Group Feedback API",
		"description": "Complete Postman collection for testing the X-Group Feedback System API.\n\n## Setup\n1. Import this collection\n2. Set the `BASE_URL` collection variable if needed (default: http://localhost:5000/api/v1)\n3. Run **Login — Super Admin** first to auto-populate tokens\n4. Use the **Login — Branch Manager** request to set `BRANCH_MANAGER_TOKEN`\n5. Use the **Login — Admin** request to set `ADMIN_TOKEN`\n\n## Notes\n- Refresh tokens are stateless (JWT-only, no DB storage). Logout is handled client-side by discarding the token.\n- The POST /auth/logout and POST /auth/refresh-token endpoints still work via cookies for convenience.",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
	"variable": [
		{
			"key": "BASE_URL",
			"value": "http://localhost:5000/api/v1"
		},
		{
			"key": "ACCESS_TOKEN",
			"value": ""
		},
		{
			"key": "ADMIN_TOKEN",
			"value": ""
		},
		{
			"key": "BRANCH_MANAGER_TOKEN",
			"value": ""
		},
		{
			"key": "SUPER_ADMIN_TOKEN",
			"value": ""
		}
	],
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "1. Health Check",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "✅ Server is running",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", () => {",
									"  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
									"});",
									"pm.test(\"Response has success, status, uptime, timestamp, version\", () => {",
									"  const json = pm.response.json();",
									"  pm.expect(json.success).to.be.true;",
									"  pm.expect(json.status).to.eql(\"ok\");",
									"  pm.expect(json).to.have.property(\"uptime\");",
									"  pm.expect(json).to.have.property(\"timestamp\");",
									"  pm.expect(json.version).to.eql(\"v1\");",
									"});"
								]
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{BASE_URL}}/health",
							"host": ["{{BASE_URL}}"],
							"path": ["health"]
						}
					}
				},
				{
					"name": "✅ Root endpoint",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "http://localhost:5000/",
							"host": ["http://localhost:5000"],
							"path": [""]
						}
					}
				}
			]
		},
		{
